# LineCount.csv is an append-only, one-row-per-date time series (the source of
# truth behind LineCount.xlsx). Use a union merge so that when two branches both
# append rows, Git keeps both sides instead of raising a conflict.
#
# Trade-off: a union merge can leave duplicate rows for the same date. That is
# harmless here because scripts/countLines.sh collapses duplicate dates (keeping
# the newest row) on its next run.
#
# Matched by basename, so it applies regardless of the file's directory path.
LineCount.csv merge=union
